Retail revenues in 2018 were $5.4 billion. These revenues decreased $91 million, or 1.7%, in 2018 as compared to the prior year.
The decrease in 2018 was primarily due to customer bill credits related to the Tax Reform Legislation and an accrual for a Rate
RSE refund, partially offset by an increase in fuel revenues and colder weather in the first quarter and warmer weather in the
second and third quarters 2018 as compared to the corresponding periods in 2017.
