residential KWH sales and weather-adjusted commercial KWH sales increased by 2.6% and 1.6%, respectively, largely due to
customer growth. Weather-adjusted industrial KWH sales were essentially flat primarily due to increased demand in the primary
and fabricated metal sectors, offset by decreased demand in the textiles and stone, clay, and glass sectors. Additionally, customer
usage for all customer classes increased due to the negative impacts of Hurricane Irma in 2017.
