Credit Rating Risk
At December 31, 2018, Georgia Power did not have any credit arrangements that would require material changes in payment
schedules or terminations as a result of a credit rating downgrade.
There are certain contracts that could require collateral, but not accelerated payment, in the event of a credit rating change to BBB-
and/or Baa3 or below. These contracts are for physical electricity purchases and sales, fuel purchases, fuel transportation and
storage, energy price risk management, transmission, interest rate management, and construction of new generation at Plant Vogtle
Units 3 and 4.
The maximum potential collateral requirements under these contracts at December 31, 2018 were as follows:
