Taxes Other Than Income Taxes
For the successor year ended December 31, 2018, taxes other than income taxes increased $27 million, or 14.7%, compared to the
prior year. Excluding a $4 million decrease related to the Southern Company Gas Dispositions, taxes other than income taxes
increased $31 million. This increase primarily reflects a $13 million increase in revenue tax expenses as a result of higher natural
gas revenues, a $12 million increase in Nicor Gas' invested capital tax that reflects a $7 million credit in 2017 to establish a related
regulatory asset, and a $4 million increase in property taxes.
For the successor year ended December 31, 2017, the successor period of July 1, 2016 through December 31, 2016, and the
predecessor period of January 1, 2016 through June 30, 2016, taxes other than income taxes were $184 million, $71 million, and
$99 million, respectively, which consisted primarily of revenue tax expenses, property taxes, and payroll taxes.
