operating margin, an $8 million increase in operating expenses, a $1 million increase in interest income, and a $21 million decrease
in other income (expense), net resulting in a $101 million increase in EBIT. The increase in net income also includes a $2 million
increase in interest expense, net of amounts capitalized and a $4 million increase in income tax expense. Details of the increase in
adjusted operating margin are provided in the table below. The increase in operating expenses primarily reflects higher
