Company Gas' 2017 GHG emissions were approximately 0.6 million metric tons of CO2 equivalent. The preliminary estimate of
Southern Company Gas' 2018 GHG emissions on the same basis is approximately 0.6 million metric tons of CO2 equivalent.
FERC Matters
Southern Company Gas is involved in two significant pipeline construction projects within gas pipeline investments. These
projects, along with Southern Company Gas' existing pipelines, are intended to provide diverse sources of natural gas supplies to
customers, resolve current and long-term supply planning for new capacity, enhance system reliability, and generate economic
development in the areas served. The following table provides an overview of these pipeline projects.
